race.comment: This looks wide open on paper. JENNI THE TANK (9) improved sharply, scoring by 2.25L over 2845m at Kyneton a week-and-a-half ago. Suitably placed and races forward. Anticipating another big run. STAR TESTYMONY (1) was on pace winning easily over 2400m at Swan Hill, as favourite. Has to stretch out over the longer journey, but he's on a quick backup and in good hands. ALPINE ROCKET (7) was well-supported when narrowly beaten at Morphettville over 2500m. Expect that form to stack right up. THE CLAIMANT (6) has been away a month and has switched from a Gold Coast yard. He missed a whisker last start at the Gold Coast over two miles in stronger than this and has jumped out well. A decent winning chance on song. SUNDAY BUZZ (5) went well at Kyneton, stepping up to 2845m. He also rates well enough to consider.
